Configure client, provision (optional), and deploy orchestrator

Usage:
  rascal bootstrap [flags]

Flags:
      --api-token string              API token for orchestrator (auto-generated if empty)
      --codex-auth string             local Codex auth.json path used to seed the initial stored shared credential (default "~/.codex/auth.json")
      --domain string                 orchestrator domain (e.g. rascal.example.com)
      --github-admin-token string     GitHub token with repo Webhooks (rw) and Issues (rw) for label/webhook setup
      --github-runtime-token string   GitHub token for remote runner operations (push/PR)
      --hcloud-token string           Hetzner Cloud token (or HCLOUD_TOKEN) for provisioning
  -h, --help                          help for bootstrap
      --host host                     existing server host (defaults to config host if set)
      --print-plan                    print resolved bootstrap actions and prerequisites without executing
      --provision-new                 force provisioning a new host when --hcloud-token is set
      --repo string                   default repository in OWNER/REPO form
      --server-url string             orchestrator URL (overrides --domain)
      --skip-deploy                   skip remote deployment
      --skip-webhook                  skip GitHub webhook setup
      --ssh-key string                SSH private key path for existing host deployment
      --ssh-port int                  SSH target port for existing host deployment (default 22)
      --ssh-user string               SSH target user for existing host deployment (default "root")
      --webhook-secret string         GitHub webhook secret (auto-generated if empty)
      --write-config                  write config file (default true)

Global Flags:
      --client-ssh-host string   SSH target host for API transport=ssh/auto
      --client-ssh-key string    SSH private key path for API transport=ssh/auto
      --client-ssh-port int      SSH target port for API transport=ssh/auto
      --client-ssh-user string   SSH target user for API transport=ssh/auto
      --config string            config file path (default "$HOME/.rascal/config.toml")
      --default-repo string      default repository in OWNER/REPO form
      --env-file string          env file path (fallback: ./.rascal.env if present)
      --no-color                 disable ANSI color/style output (also set by NO_COLOR)
      --output string            output format: table|json|toml (default "table")
  -q, --quiet                    reduce non-essential output
      --transport string         API transport: auto|http|ssh
